To calculate the average dependency distance for the sentence "Prestationen mätes i huvudsak av hur stor kundnyttan är, där en av aspekterna är distributionsnätens tillgänglighet.", we first need to identify the dependencies and their distances.

1. Identify the dependencies:
   - "Prestationen" (subject) depends on "mätes" (head) → distance = 1
   - "mätes" (head) depends on "i" (preposition) → distance = 1
   - "i" depends on "huvudsak" (object of the preposition) → distance = 1
   - "huvudsak" depends on "av" (preposition) → distance = 1
   - "av" depends on "hur" (how) → distance = 1
   - "hur" depends on "stor" (adjective) → distance = 2
   - "stor" depends on "kundnyttan" (subject of second clause) → distance = 2
   - "kundnyttan" depends on "är" (verb) → distance = 1
   - "är" depends on "," (punctuation) → distance = 1
   - "där" depends on "," (punctuation) → distance = 3
   - "en" depends on "aspekterna" (object) → distance = 2
   - "aspekterna" depends on "är" (following verb) → distance = 1
   - "är" depends on "distributionsnätens" → distance = 0
   - "distributionsnätens" depends on "tillgänglighet" (complement) → distance = 1
   - "tillgänglighet" has no further dependencies and is the last token.

